questions.model_answer:
\textbf{Part (a)}

\qquad Multiply by the scale factor from inches to cm:

$$ 3 \times 2.54 = 7.62 $$ cm \hfill (1)

\vspace{0.3cm}
\textbf{Part (b)}

\qquad Divide by the scale factor from cm to inches:

$$ 50 \div 2.54 = 19.69 $$ inches \hfill (2)
\vspace{0.3cm}

questions.content:
You can use this graph to change between inches and cm.

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.5]

  \draw[step=0.5cm, very thin, gray!50] (0,0) grid (20,28);
  \draw[step=4cm, thick, gray!80] (0,0) grid (20,28);
  \draw[->, thick] (0,0) -- (0,29);
  \draw[->, thick] (0,0) -- (21,0);

  \node at (-3,14.5) {\text{cm}};
  \node at (10.5,-2.4) {\text{inches}};

  \draw[thick] (0,0) -- (20,50.8);

\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

\begin{enumerate}
  \item[(a)] Change 3 inches to cm 

  \vspace{1cm}
  \hfill \makebox[5cm]{\dotfill} cm 
  \hfill (1)

  \item[(b)] Change 50 cm to inches 

  \vspace{2cm}
  \hfill \makebox[5cm]{\dotfill} inches 
  \hfill (2)
\end{enumerate}

